name: Marinated Chicken Kabobs
author: D.DETMANN
summary: This great summer recipe was given to me by a friend years ago. You can put any vegetables you want on the skewers. Don't be worried when you see the light corn syrup in the ingredients, it comes together great! It's a great change. You can even skip the vegetables and just skewer the chicken. Enjoy!
ingredients: 4  skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces
1  green bell pepper, cut into large chunks
directions: In a medium bowl, blend vegetable oil, soy sauce, light corn syrup, lemon juice, sesame seeds, garlic powder, and garlic salt
Cover, and marinate in the refrigerator at least 2 hours
Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat, and lightly oil grate
Thread chicken onto skewers alternately with mushrooms, onions, and green bell pepper
Pour marinade into a saucepan, and bring to a boil
Place skewers on the prepared grill
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, turning frequently, until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear
Baste with the boiled marinade frequently during the last 10 minutes
